.el .ds Aq '
.TH qork 1  "qork 1.1.1"
.SH NAME
qork \- Shorten URLs from your terminal — the qork.me client
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBqork\fR [\fB\-a\fR|\fB\-\-alias\fR] [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-color\fR] [\fB\-\-api\-base\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-check\fR] [\fB\-\-update\fR] [\fB\-\-uninstall\fR] [\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] [\fIURL\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
qork shortens a URL by calling the qork.me API and prints the short link.
.PP
Paste a normal URL straight in:
    qork https://example.com/some/very/long/path
.PP
If the URL has spaces or shell\-special characters, wrap it in quotes:
    qork "https://example.com/a b?x=1&y=2"
.PP
Use \-\-alias for a custom code, \-\-json for machine\-readable output, and
`qork update` / `qork uninstall` / `qork help` to manage the install.
.PP
Before shortening, qork sanity\-checks that the URL is a real, reachable
link (a quick HEAD request); pass \-\-no\-check to skip that.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-alias\fR \fI<ALIAS>\fR
Request a custom short code (alias) instead of a generated one
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Print the raw JSON response (for scripts and agents)
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-color\fR
Disable colored output
.TP
\fB\-\-api\-base\fR \fI<URL>\fR
API base URL to call (default: https://qork.me)
.RS
May also be specified with the \fBQORK_API_BASE\fR environment variable.
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-check\fR
Skip the pre\-shorten check (don\*(Aqt verify the URL is a real, live link)
.TP
\fB\-\-update\fR
Check for a newer release and update qork in place
.TP
\fB\-\-uninstall\fR
Remove qork from this machine
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-yes\fR
Skip the interactive confirmation prompt (for `uninstall`). Required when stdin isn\*(Aqt a terminal (scripts/CI) so removal is always explicit
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.TP
[\fIURL\fR]
The URL to shorten (wrap in quotes if it has spaces or special characters). The bare words `update`, `uninstall`, and `help` run those commands instead
